# Hermes profile runtime state (generated by a booted agent: credential pool,
# session transcripts, caches). Never commit — auth.json references live keys.
#
# Allowlist, not a denylist: a booted agent drops whatever directories the
# upstream runtime wants into a profile, so naming them one by one loses the
# race. An earlier denylist here covered auth/cache/logs/sessions/memories/
# audio_cache/image_cache and was already missing cron, hooks, pairing, skills,
# and .skills_prompt_snapshot.json by the time it landed. Only the three
# authored files below are tracked, so anything new the runtime writes is
# ignored by default rather than silently committable — which is the behaviour
# you want for a directory that holds credentials.
#
# Adding a genuinely authored profile file? Add a matching negation. `git add`
# refuses ignored paths loudly, so this fails visibly rather than silently.
hermes/profiles/*/*
!hermes/profiles/*/.env.example
!hermes/profiles/*/SOUL.md
!hermes/profiles/*/config.yaml
